transcription.text:
Speaker 1: David calling Viagra, this is Jimmy.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I need to cancel my prescription that I have with you guys.

Speaker 2: Okay, let me see if I can pull you up with your phone number and try to take care of that for you.

Speaker 1: It's 513.

Speaker 2: No, I think I have it, David. I was able to get that pulled up with the information that I'm calling from.

Speaker 1: All right, give me one second.

Speaker 2: Let me go ahead and try to take care of your request for you.

Speaker 1: I see you're getting the Viagra, the 100 milligram.

Speaker 2: It looks like that's your prescription, how you're getting 10 every month.

Speaker 1: Is that too frequently for you, or is it particularly why you want to cancel?

Speaker 2: I just don't need them. I'm good.

Speaker 1: All right, not a problem. Let me go ahead and take care of your request.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, David, what I was able to go ahead and do for you, I was able to stop those monthly shipments. I also stopped the monthly refills that was included with your prescription, and I stopped the monthly charges as well.

Speaker 2: It looks like you did just recently have one shipped out to you just on the 12th, it looks like, too, as well.

Speaker 1: Let me ask you, how were the refills working for you when you were using them?

Speaker 2: They were fine. I just don't need them anymore. I'm good.

Speaker 1: Okay, but I have one of the latest ones that's already shipped out, but I made sure going forward you won't get any more sent out to you as far as I'm concerned.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you very much.

Speaker 2: Take care.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right, bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
